@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About PdfToolStack — PDF Workflows That Just Work</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="PdfToolStack helps people compress, convert, sign, secure, and automate PDFs without installing software. Learn why we built a privacy-first PDF workflow platform." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://pdftoolstack.com/about" />
</HeadContent>

<main class="about-page">
    <section class="about-hero">
        <div class="about-hero-copy">
            <span class="about-eyebrow">About PdfToolStack</span>
            <h1>PDF workflows that just work.</h1>
            <p>
                PdfToolStack helps people compress, convert, sign, secure, and automate documents without installing software.
            </p>
            <div class="about-actions">
                <a href="/" class="about-btn about-btn-primary">Explore tools</a>
                <a href="/contact" class="about-btn about-btn-secondary">Contact us</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-hero-card" aria-label="PdfToolStack workflow promise">
            <div class="about-flow-card">
                <span>Upload</span>
                <strong>PDF</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="about-flow-line"></div>
            <div class="about-flow-card about-flow-card-accent">
                <span>Choose</span>
                <strong>Workflow</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="about-flow-line"></div>
            <div class="about-flow-card about-flow-card-done">
                <span>Download</span>
                <strong>Result</strong>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-trust-strip" aria-label="Trust and privacy">
        <div>
            <strong>Secure uploads</strong>
            <span>Protected document transfer</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>Auto-delete after 1 hour</strong>
            <span>Temporary files do not linger</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>No permanent storage</strong>
            <span>Your documents stay yours</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>No signup for basic tools</strong>
            <span>Start without friction</span>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section about-story-section">
        <div class="about-section-heading">
            <span class="about-eyebrow">Why we built it</span>
            <h2>PDF tools should feel simple, private, and reliable.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="about-story-grid">
            <article class="about-story-card">
                <h3>Built from real document work</h3>
                <p>
                    PdfToolStack started after years of dealing with healthcare IT reports, forms, audit documents, and secure workflows where mistakes matter.
                </p>
            </article>
            <article class="about-story-card">
                <h3>No mid-task surprises</h3>
                <p>
                    The goal is straightforward: upload a file, finish the task, and download the result without surprise watermarks or signup walls on basic tools.
                </p>
            </article>
            <article class="about-story-card">
                <h3>Privacy by default</h3>
                <p>
                    Documents often contain contracts, invoices, financial details, and personal information. Files are processed for the task and deleted automatically.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <div class="about-section-heading">
            <span class="about-eyebrow">Who it’s for</span>
            <h2>Built for people who move documents all day.</h2>
            <p>
                PdfToolStack is designed for teams and individuals who need practical PDF workflows without heavy desktop software.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-audience-grid">
            <div class="about-audience-card">
                <strong>Operations teams</strong>
                <span>Compress, merge, organize, and batch process recurring document work.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="about-audience-card">
                <strong>Finance and accounting</strong>
                <span>Convert documents, extract invoice data, and prepare clean spreadsheets.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="about-audience-card">
                <strong>Legal and HR</strong>
                <span>Sign, redact, compare, review, and securely share important documents.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="about-audience-card">
                <strong>Everyday PDF fixes</strong>
                <span>Make files smaller, editable, printable, searchable, and easier to send.</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section about-principles">
        <div class="about-section-heading">
            <span class="about-eyebrow">Product principles</span>
            <h2>Practical software, not PDF theater.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="about-principle-list">
            <div>
                <span>01</span>
                <strong>Fast workflows</strong>
                <p>Tools should guide you from upload to result with as little friction as possible.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <span>02</span>
                <strong>Transparent value</strong>
                <p>Basic tools should be genuinely useful. Pro adds larger files, AI workflows, and batch processing.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <span>03</span>
                <strong>Security-first defaults</strong>
                <p>Privacy, temporary processing, and automatic cleanup are part of the product foundation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-final-cta">
        <div>
            <span class="about-eyebrow">Start now</span>
            <h2>Ready to fix your next PDF?</h2>
            <p>Choose a workflow, upload your file, and download the finished document.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-actions">
            <a href="/" class="about-btn about-btn-primary">Explore tools</a>
            <a href="/pricing" class="about-btn about-btn-secondary">View pricing</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>
